<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFF26FA40FEEBFA44" bold="true" box="[136,292,1470,1496]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFBE850DFEEFFA40FE5CFA44" box="[321,403,1470,1496]" name="Bolivia" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFBE850DFE67FA41FDCFFA45" box="[457,512,1471,1497]" name="Peru" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8628475BFFBE850DFF13FA1CFBDFF92C" blockId="25.[136,1452,1470,1713]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFF13FA1CFEE9FA60" bold="true" box="[189,294,1506,1532]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">Notes:—</emphasis>
This species generally produces huge, erect or pendent, pseudo-terrestrial proliferous plants. It is similar to 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFF06F9F9FEDBF9BC" box="[168,276,1542,1568]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBE850DFF06F9F9FEDFF9BC" authorityName="Luer &amp; Vasquez" authorityYear="1980" box="[168,272,1542,1568]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chloe">M. chloe</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which is also found in 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFBE850DFD81F9F8FD4AF9BC" box="[559,645,1542,1568]" name="Bolivia" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. However, it can be distinguished from that species by the yellowish to brownish flowers and obscurely angled lip margins 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFD51F9D5FCD9F9D8" box="[767,790,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">vs</emphasis>
. whitish flowers and acute lateral lobes of the lip. In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFBE850DFE89F9B1FDACF9F4" authority=", Schlechter (1912)" authorityName=", Schlechter" authorityYear="1912" box="[295,611,1614,1641]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutex">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFBE850DFE89F9B1FE42F9F4" box="[295,397,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">M. frutex</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFFBE850DFE35F9B0FDACF9F4" author="Schlechter, R." box="[411,611,1614,1640]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" pagination="417 - 464" refId="ref31484" refString="Schlechter, R. (1912) Orchidaceae novae et criticae. Decas XXI - XXIII. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 10: 417 - 464. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19120103009" type="journal article" year="1912">Schlechter (1912)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
did not indicate where the 
<typeStatus id="592CF9F9FFBE850DFC3DF9B0FC3AF9F4" box="[915,1013,1614,1640]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">holotype</typeStatus>
was preserved. Assuming the 
<typeStatus id="592CF9F9FFBE850DFAE7F9B0FA64F9F4" box="[1353,1451,1614,1640]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">holotype</typeStatus>
was in Berlin and was lost when the herbarium was destroyed, 
<bibRefCitation id="E2063AAAFFBE850DFCECF98DFC07F910" author="Luer, C. A." box="[834,968,1650,1677]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref29681" refString="Luer, C. A. (1992) Icones pleurothallidinarum IX. Systematic of Myoxanthus. Addenda to Platystele, Pleurothallis, subgenus Scopula and Scaphosepalum (Orchidaceae). Monographs in Systematic Botany, Missouri Botanical Garden 44: 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Luer (1992)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the location of a type at K, but he did not designate it explicitly as a 
<typeStatus id="592CF9F9FFBE850DFDA9F968FDBEF92C" box="[519,625,1686,1712]" pageId="25" pageNumber="236">lectotype</typeStatus>
. We thus make this designation here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
